---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/shared/Container.astro';
import MonoEyebrow from '../../components/shared/MonoEyebrow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Blue Business"
  description="Privacy Policy of Blue Innovation B.V. (Blue Business). How we collect, use and protect data in accordance with GDPR."
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy/"
>
  <section class="pt-[140px] md:pt-[180px] pb-10">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <MonoEyebrow text="// Legal" tone="accent-hi" class="mb-5 block" />
      <h1 class="text-h1 font-medium" style="letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight); line-height: 1.02;">
        <span class="block text-fg">Privacy</span>
        <span class="block text-accent">Policy.</span>
      </h1>
      <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-[10px] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/[0.06] border border-[var(--color-accent-line)] max-w-[60ch]">
        <p class="text-[14px] text-fg-dim">
          This is an informational English translation. The legally binding version is the Dutch Privacy Policy. <a href="/nl/privacy/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Read the Dutch version</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-24">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-[15px] text-fg-dim" style="line-height: 1.7;">
        <p>
          This is the Privacy Policy of Blue Innovation B.V. (hereafter "Bluebusiness", "we", "us" or "our"), a company with registered address Rietsingel 46, Zwaanshoek, the Netherlands. Bluebusiness is registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce under number 80387578. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share and protect data in relation to our services. We collect this data when you use our services. We process personal data in a manner consistent with the General Data Protection Regulation ("GDPR"), the GDPR-based implementing legislation and other applicable privacy law.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our Privacy Policy applies to anyone who uses our services. By using our services, you understand and agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this privacy policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">What data do we collect?</h2>
        <p>
          We collect personal data that you provide to us. Personal data means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-[lower-alpha] pl-6 space-y-1.5">
          <li>Contact and address information</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Financial information</li>
          <li>Account information</li>
          <li>Other personal data you provide</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Purposes of data processing</h2>
        <p>
          By using our services, you leave certain data with us, for example by creating an account. This may include information such as name, email address, phone number and payment details. Bluebusiness collects and processes this data to make our services accessible. We also collect information about your device (such as IP address and browser type) so we can improve our services. Personal data is not shared with third parties unless we are required to do so by law.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">How is this information shared?</h2>
        <p>
          We will not rent or sell your personal data to third parties unless you give us permission or to comply with a legal obligation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Legal requests and harm prevention</h2>
        <p>
          On the basis of a legal request, we are entitled to access your information and retain and/or share it in response to a legal request (such as a search warrant, court order or subpoena). We are also entitled to retain and/or share your information where we believe this is necessary to detect, prevent and address fraud or other illegal activity, and to protect ourselves, you and others. Information we receive about you may be accessed, processed and retained for a longer period where necessary due to a legal request or obligation, an investigation concerning our terms or policies, or to otherwise prevent harm.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Security</h2>
        <p>
          Bluebusiness has implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against any form of unlawful processing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Website disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          By using the website you agree to the disclaimer. Bluebusiness reserves the right to change the content of its website and/or this disclaimer at any time without informing its clients and/or users of the website. The content of the website has been compiled with the greatest possible care, but may nevertheless contain inaccuracies or be incomplete. Bluebusiness accepts no liability whatsoever for any damage arising from or resulting from the use of the website. The use of this website is entirely at the user's own expense and risk. No rights can be derived from the content of the website. All texts on the website are protected by copyright and owned by Bluebusiness insofar as they do not belong to third parties.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Cookie statement</h2>
        <p>
          Bluebusiness uses technical and functional cookies to optimize the website. Cookies are small text files sent along when visiting a website to make visitors' user experiences more efficient. Under applicable law, Bluebusiness may store cookies on your device if these cookies are strictly necessary to operate the website. For other types of cookies, your consent is required. We recommend accepting cookies for website usability. Bluebusiness uses functional cookies that ensure the website functions properly. These cookies have no effect on personal privacy, so consent is not required. The Bluebusiness website also uses Google Analytics cookies. If you have questions, contact <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Social media use</h2>
        <p>
          Bluebusiness uses third-party cookies to optimize the website. Some cookies are placed by third-party services displayed on the website. Third parties include Google Analytics and social media (Instagram, Facebook, Twitter and Youtube). The privacy and cookie policy of the relevant company applies to the use of cookies from other companies (third parties). For cookies from social media parties and the data and/or personal data they collect, Bluebusiness refers you to the privacy and cookie statements of those parties.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Retention</h2>
        <p>
          In accordance with the GDPR and other applicable legislation, Bluebusiness does not retain personal data longer than necessary for achieving the purposes for which it is collected or processed. If you want more information on how long your specific personal data is retained, contact <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Right of access, correction, objection and data portability</h2>
        <p>
          If you wish to access your personal data, change or delete your data, or transfer your personal data in whole or in part to yourself or a third party, you can contact us by emailing <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you object to the way we handle your data, you can file a complaint with the Dutch Data Protection Authority (Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens).
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Changes</h2>
        <p>
          Bluebusiness may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. You are therefore advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly. Changes to this Privacy Policy take effect at the moment they are published on our website.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact Bluebusiness by emailing <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
